  text: What’s wrong in your VBA is this line:

```vb
c.Value = ("C2") = Left(ws.Range("C2"), Len(ws.Range("C2")) - 3)
```

You’re not assigning the trimmed text to each cell. Instead, VBA evaluates this as a comparison:

```vb
("C2") = Left(...)
```

That comparison returns `True` or `False`, and then you assign that boolean result into `c.Value`. Since `"C2"` will almost never equal the postcode text, every cell becomes `FALSE`.

