# row-wise-positive-minimum-header-backmapping

**When to use**: A row contains multiple candidate value columns and the required output is the header label of the best qualifying value, possibly with ties.

**Why it works**: This technique succeeded in all rollouts because it separates value comparison from header retrieval, preserving correct tie handling and avoiding fragile formula-dependent logic.

