  text: Use a right-to-left loop so column deletions do not shift the remaining columns before you inspect them.

VBA:
```vb
Sub DeleteDescriptionColumns()
    Dim ws As Worksheet
    Dim lastCol As Long
    Dim c As Long

    Set ws = ActiveSheet
    lastCol = ws.Cells(1, ws.Columns.Count).End(xlToLeft).Column

    For c = lastCol To 1 Step -1
        If InStr(1, CStr(ws.Cells(1, c).Value), "/description", vbTextCompare) > 0 Then
            ws.Columns(c).Delete
        End If
    Next c
End Sub
```

